This paper involves the use of a biomimetic autonomous robot to study animal behaviour, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of behavioural models and real-time calibration, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of evolutionary algorithms for calibration is also a topic in machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the paper mentions individual tracking and data analysis, which are topics in computer vision (cs.CV).
